President Muhammadu Buhari has directed the Attorney General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami, to take immediate steps to publish the Presidential Order on June 12 as Democracy Day in the Federal Gazette.
This followed his declaration on Wednesday that henceforth, June 12 be observed as Nigeria’s Democracy Day and that some heroes of democracy be given national honours,  
A statement by presidential spokesman, Garba Shehu, yesterday said the president directed that the Order be published as follows: “Chief MKO Abiola - Grand Commander of the Federal Republic (Posthumous).
“Ambassador Baba Gana Kingibe - Grand Commander of the Order of the Niger.
“Chief Gani Fawehinmi       -Grand Commander of the Order of the Niger (Posthumous)”
He said the president also directed that this should be done so that the awards slated for June 12, 2018 could go on as planned.